# Summary

The LLM Architecture provides a provider-independent abstraction that isolates all model-specific behaviour from the review architectures.

This allows Agentless, Hierarchical, and Consensus to reuse the same prompt infrastructure, metrics collection, and provider interface while supporting future LLM providers without architectural changes.
